<NEW>

The ground does not readilly flaten out at first, in fact for a while
it only gets worse as the underbrush grows densly in this region.
However as they trees thicken and reclaim the canopy then the
underbrush finally began to loose its hold, giving room for open
driving should WHEELIE choose to do so.

In the distance the sound of laser fire could be just made out then
something cracking could be heard and the the sound of something large
falling to the ground. It was all some distance away . . .

(TAG)

- Preston
